    "problemStatement": "You are given a prime number PPP and two integers A,BA, BA,B. Your task is to find the minimum value of (AT⋅B) mod P(A^T \\cdot B) \\bmod{P}(AT⋅B)modP over all nonnegative integers TTT.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe only line of input contains three space-separated integers P,A,BP, A, BP,A,B.\nIt's guaranteed that PPP is prime.\n\n\nOutput Format\nOutput the minimum value of (AT⋅B) mod P(A^T \\cdot B) \\bmod P(AT⋅B)modP over all nonnegative integers TTT.",
    "constraints": [
      "3≤P≤10133 \\le P \\le 10^{13}3≤P≤1013",
      "1≤A,B&lt;P1 \\le A, B \\lt P1≤A,B&lt;P",
      "PPP is a prime number.",
      "Subtasks",
      "**Subtask 1 (5 points):**",
      "P≤107P \\le 10^7P≤107",
      "**Subtask 2 (20 points):**",
      "P≤109P \\le 10^9P≤109",
      "**Subtask 3 (25 points):**",
      "P≤1011P \\le 10^{11}P≤1011",
      "**Subtask 4 (20 points):**",
      "P≤1012P \\le 10^{12}P≤1012",
      "**Subtask 5 (30 points):**",
      "Original constraints."
